231
00:20:21.250 --> 00:20:23.419
Should we discuss it more?

232
00:20:24.849 --> 00:20:27.050
It's much less than what you expected.

233
00:20:27.320 --> 00:20:28.419
No.

234
00:20:29.590 --> 00:20:31.459
I think it's too much.

235
00:20:35.699 --> 00:20:36.859
Ms. Yoon.

236
00:20:37.869 --> 00:20:39.330
You shouldn't do that.

237
00:20:40.129 --> 00:20:41.270
What?

238
00:20:41.699 --> 00:20:45.109
Even if you're surprised, you should go outside and express it alone.

239
00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:47.169
We're going under a contract.

240
00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:50.010
You can't express yourself so honestly to your enemy.

241
00:20:54.649 --> 00:20:56.149
You're...

242
00:20:57.619 --> 00:20:59.320
not my enemy.

243
00:21:03.389 --> 00:21:04.859
It's not much.

244
00:21:06.060 --> 00:21:09.800
It's the amount we mostly offer to our new writers.

245
00:21:10.730 --> 00:21:14.340
We don't sign contracts with writers that often to be honest.

246
00:21:15.540 --> 00:21:19.169
