555
00:43:52.160 --> 00:43:54.100
So this marriage makes it hard for people to easily break up...

556
00:43:54.859 --> 00:43:57.829
even if they don't have feelings for each other anymore.

557
00:43:59.470 --> 00:44:00.800
I don't know.

558
00:44:02.070 --> 00:44:03.970
It's my first time getting married.

559
00:44:06.939 --> 00:44:08.109
It's my first time loving someone too.

560
00:44:12.910 --> 00:44:14.950
So I don't know much about this.

561
00:44:17.890 --> 00:44:19.590
I know one thing for sure.

562
00:44:23.359 --> 00:44:25.930
Winning someone's heart is not a game.

563
00:44:28.930 --> 00:44:30.160
It rather comes naturally.

564
00:44:38.470 --> 00:44:40.010
Please don't tell Se Hee...

565
00:44:41.709 --> 00:44:43.979
that I know what happened.

566
00:45:09.039 --> 00:45:10.240
Good bye.

567
00:45:10.939 --> 00:45:14.039
Go back to your life and live well.

568
00:45:15.140 --> 00:45:16.780
Instead,

569
00:45:18.079 --> 00:45:19.709
don't ever fall for anyone.

570
00:45:21.479 --> 00:45:25.019
You don't have the right to.

571
00:45:25.019 --> 00:45:28.990
(You don't have the right to love.)

572
00:45:32.260 --> 00:45:33.530
So she's right.

573
00:45:34.499 --> 00:45:36.959
Winning someone's heart is not a game.

574
00:45:39.070 --> 00:45:40.669
She knew it so quickly.

575
00:45:42.600 --> 00:45:44.870
How I wish I was Ji Ho.

576
00:45:51.979 --> 00:45:53.350
Your call was long.

577
00:45:53.479 --> 00:45:55.419
Yes, it was the lawyer.

578
00:45:55.879 --> 00:45:58.149
There have been some problems with Ji Ho's lawsuit against the guy.

579
00:45:58.220 --> 00:46:00.590
What? What kind of problem?

580
00:46:00.590 --> 00:46:01.620
Well.

581
00:46:02.620 --> 00:46:05.160
The guy went to ask for the charges to be dropped.

582
00:46:05.390 --> 00:46:08.829
But he got beaten up really hard.

583
00:46:10.629 --> 00:46:12.100
By whom?

584
00:46:12.269 --> 00:46:13.970
Ji Ho's husband.

585
00:46:14.070 --> 00:46:15.169
What?

586
00:46:15.840 --> 00:46:19.039
You mean he beat someone up?

587
00:46:19.510 --> 00:46:22.010
- It's been long! - Yes, it has been really long.

588
00:46:22.010 --> 00:46:23.879
You did a good job this year.

589
00:46:24.410 --> 00:46:26.010
- Let's do well again next year. - Yes, sir.

590
00:46:26.010 --> 00:46:29.450
Everyone, let me propose a toast.

591
00:46:29.850 --> 00:46:31.950
Fill in your empty glasses.

592
00:46:32.490 --> 00:46:34.890
- Why don't you give a toast? - Yes, sir.

593
00:46:36.620 --> 00:46:38.930
2017 is almost over.

594
00:46:39.129 --> 00:46:40.590
Our respected director,

595
00:46:40.959 --> 00:46:42.800
I love you, sir!

596
00:46:43.629 --> 00:46:47.070
And to our business supporting team, you all have done a good job.

597
00:46:47.470 --> 00:46:50.640
Let's toast for our most respected director with all our hearts.

598
00:46:50.809 --> 00:46:52.840
When I say "Director!",

599
00:46:53.010 --> 00:46:55.579
you all say "I love you, sir!"

600
00:46:56.079 --> 00:46:58.510
I forgot about the apology.

601
00:46:59.680 --> 00:47:00.820
I'm sorry, Ms. Woo.

602
00:47:01.249 --> 00:47:02.649
I have been very naughty.

603
00:47:02.919 --> 00:47:05.919
Let's all forget about it with our drinks.

604
00:47:07.459 --> 00:47:09.620
I'll say "Director!"

605
00:47:09.859 --> 00:47:11.530
- I love you, sir! - I love you, sir!

606
00:47:11.530 --> 00:47:12.930
I love you all, too!

607
00:47:13.459 --> 00:47:16.300
- Drink it up. - Bottoms up.

608
00:47:16.300 --> 00:47:17.829
Do you need more drinks?

609
00:47:17.829 --> 00:47:19.499
- Where shall we go next? - Second round sounds good.

610
00:47:19.870 --> 00:47:21.870
Was there anything between you two?

611
00:47:21.870 --> 00:47:23.800
No, nothing happened.

612
00:47:24.109 --> 00:47:25.169
Have your food.

613
00:47:26.410 --> 00:47:28.680
- Drink it up. - Let's all drink.

614
00:47:28.740 --> 00:47:30.649
Pass me the glass.

615
00:47:32.809 --> 00:47:35.050
- I'll go home first. - See you tomorrow, sir.

616
00:47:35.050 --> 00:47:36.879
- Don't get late to work. - We won't!

617
00:47:37.249 --> 00:47:39.090
- Bye. - See you all tomorrow.

618
00:47:41.320 --> 00:47:44.189
- How about we have more drinks? - Sure!

619
00:47:45.059 --> 00:47:47.329
Let's eat some beef sashimi and go for karaoke afterwards.

620
00:47:47.359 --> 00:47:49.800
- Okay, sure. Karaoke sounds fun. - I'll drop by the office first.

621
00:47:50.160 --> 00:47:52.169
You all wait here.

622
00:47:52.200 --> 00:47:54.070
- Meet us at the beef sashimi place. - See you later.

623
00:48:01.609 --> 00:48:03.240
Alright! It's a desert island!

624
00:48:07.720 --> 00:48:09.979
Whose turn is it next?

625
00:48:10.180 --> 00:48:11.289
Hi, babe.

626
00:48:11.289 --> 00:48:13.590
Isn't language for humans?

627
00:48:14.189 --> 00:48:15.220
You're right.

628
00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:18.059
Languages only work for humans. Am I right?

629
00:48:18.359 --> 00:48:20.829
You're right. If language doesn't work for someone, he's not a human.

630
00:48:20.829 --> 00:48:23.829
Either he's an animal, an insect, or a water flea.

631
00:48:24.269 --> 00:48:25.329
Why do you ask?

632
00:48:25.329 --> 00:48:26.430
Honey.

633
00:48:27.300 --> 00:48:30.769
Did you mean it when you said you'll stand by me once I start?

634
00:48:31.240 --> 00:48:33.709
- Of course, I meant it. - What are you doing Mr. Ma?

635
00:48:33.709 --> 00:48:35.879
- It's your turn to roll. - Throw the dice.

636
00:48:36.379 --> 00:48:37.550
Mr. Ma!

637
00:48:37.550 --> 00:48:40.180
Okay. Have fun playing with dice.

638
00:48:44.649 --> 00:48:45.820
I love you.

639
00:48:50.629 --> 00:48:53.030
Hello? Hello?

640
00:48:57.329 --> 00:49:00.269
What is this supposed to be? It sounds like a will.

641
00:49:00.430 --> 00:49:02.840
Mr. Ma, it's your turn. Come on! Throw the dice.

642
00:49:07.039 --> 00:49:08.510
- Is it Seoul? - She can't be...

643
00:49:08.510 --> 00:49:09.879
Goodness, I lost.

644
00:49:10.079 --> 00:49:12.379
No. No. No. No.

645
00:49:12.379 --> 00:49:13.709
What do you mean?

646
00:49:13.709 --> 00:49:16.879
Mr. Ma, you have to buy Seoul now.

647
00:49:22.059 --> 00:49:23.720
Coward.

648
00:49:41.579 --> 00:49:44.510
Ms. Woo should upload the photo of her body.

649
00:49:45.749 --> 00:49:47.879
B? B? No. No. No.

650
00:49:47.879 --> 00:49:51.220
It's full size A.

651
00:49:51.350 --> 00:49:53.919
If I weren't married,

652
00:49:53.919 --> 00:49:57.220
I would have had fun with Ms. Woo.

653
00:50:12.109 --> 00:50:14.309
Ms. Woo, why did you come back to the office?

654
00:50:14.309 --> 00:50:16.640
I have some undone work.

655
00:50:17.579 --> 00:50:18.680
Really?

656
00:50:24.050 --> 00:50:26.120
- Jin Ho! - What did you say?

657
00:50:45.269 --> 00:50:47.809
I'll roll the dice now.

658
00:50:50.309 --> 00:50:51.709
I'm buying Taipei.

659
00:50:51.709 --> 00:50:53.680
I was going to buy that.

660
00:50:53.680 --> 00:50:56.680
A rabbit is the king when the tiger is not around.

661
00:50:56.680 --> 00:50:59.249
Is this all your land?

662
00:50:59.249 --> 00:51:02.419
We have raised a baby tiger.

663
00:51:02.419 --> 00:51:04.859
That's what I mean. You should have bought it.

664
00:51:04.859 --> 00:51:07.430
You'll only catch the tiger if you go into the tiger's cave.

665
00:51:07.700 --> 00:51:08.959
Let's stop playing this game.

666
00:51:08.959 --> 00:51:11.030
Why? It's getting fun.

667
00:51:11.030 --> 00:51:12.470
It's not fun at all. It's for kids.

668
00:51:12.470 --> 00:51:13.729
We're always playing this.

669
00:51:13.729 --> 00:51:15.840
Let's all go drink. I'll treat tonight.

670
00:51:16.370 --> 00:51:17.669
- Really? - Your treat?

671
00:51:17.669 --> 00:51:20.470
Yes, I'll buy you all drinks. Let's stay up until the dawn.

672
00:51:21.010 --> 00:51:22.840
I'll leave first then.

673
00:51:23.209 --> 00:51:24.879
You should go with us too.

674
00:51:25.379 --> 00:51:27.350
It's okay. I have an appointment.

675
00:51:27.350 --> 00:51:29.479
What kind of appointment do you have at this hour?

676
00:51:29.850 --> 00:51:31.320
It's an appointment with myself.

677
00:51:31.850 --> 00:51:33.490
You all have fun. I'll go now.

678
00:51:36.720 --> 00:51:38.490
It's Friday, right?

679
00:51:38.490 --> 00:51:40.160
She must be going to Itaewon.

680
00:51:40.459 --> 00:51:44.100
- Itaewon? - There's a famous toy shop there.

681
00:51:44.100 --> 00:51:46.629
She goes there every Friday...

682
00:51:46.629 --> 00:51:47.769
buying all the cartoon figures.

683
00:51:48.939 --> 00:51:50.340
It suits her really well.

684
00:51:51.809 --> 00:51:54.010
Speaking of Itaewon,

685
00:51:54.280 --> 00:51:55.939
let's go clubbing tonight. What about men's night out?

686
00:51:56.439 --> 00:51:58.309
- Club? - Club?

687
00:51:58.309 --> 00:52:01.550
Yes, club! What will you do with your body? Make use of it.

688
00:52:01.550 --> 00:52:03.649
You should enjoy it when you can as you're still single.

689
00:52:04.390 --> 00:52:06.749
Have you been to clubs a lot?

690
00:52:07.559 --> 00:52:09.220
No, I have never been.

691
00:52:29.240 --> 00:52:31.010
My ears are going to bleed!

692
00:52:31.010 --> 00:52:33.280
I didn't know it's like this here.

693
00:52:34.419 --> 00:52:36.379
My eyes are going to bleed.

694
00:52:46.629 --> 00:52:49.729
Let's all go out and dance on the stage.

695
00:52:49.729 --> 00:52:50.870
What?

696
00:52:50.870 --> 00:52:53.470
- No, no. - You should go first.

697
00:52:53.470 --> 00:52:56.140
I'll go downstairs first. You two come down too.

698
00:52:56.140 --> 00:52:57.910
- Yes. - We'll follow you.

699
00:52:57.910 --> 00:52:59.070
I'll go down first.

700
00:52:59.070 --> 00:53:00.169
Okay.

701
00:53:06.510 --> 00:53:08.749
I'll get over you.

702
00:53:09.220 --> 00:53:10.749
I'll get over you, Ho Rang!

703
00:53:11.289 --> 00:53:13.550
I'll get over you!

704
00:54:07.010 --> 00:54:08.280
That guy?

705
00:54:08.280 --> 00:54:09.680
What is that guy doing there?

706
00:54:10.879 --> 00:54:12.149
Bo Mi!

707
00:54:13.379 --> 00:54:15.519
Come down!

708
00:54:15.979 --> 00:54:18.189
I'm too scared.

709
00:54:18.189 --> 00:54:20.919
Do you want to go to an internet cafe? Let's go.

710
00:54:23.919 --> 00:54:27.959
You said you had an appointment.

711
00:54:29.729 --> 00:54:33.070
We talk with our bodies on the stage.

712
00:54:34.539 --> 00:54:35.640
Bodies?

713
00:54:53.653 --> 00:54:56.124
Se Hee,

714
00:54:56.423 --> 00:54:59.934
can I ask you two favors?

715
00:55:00.633 --> 00:55:05.503
Could you let Ji Ho write...

716
00:55:06.334 --> 00:55:09.104
when she asks you if she can?

717
00:55:09.874 --> 00:55:13.044
Could you please...

718
00:55:14.184 --> 00:55:17.383
make her fulfill her dream...

719
00:55:18.713 --> 00:55:20.624
as a writer and...

720
00:55:21.454 --> 00:55:23.084
not live like her own mom?

721
00:55:32.834 --> 00:55:35.834
(Ko Jung Min)

722
00:55:40.003 --> 00:55:41.144
Hello?

723
00:56:00.994 --> 00:56:02.664
(Writing Contract)

724
00:56:10.463 --> 00:56:13.503
(Korean authors, Foreign authors)

725
00:56:24.454 --> 00:56:28.983
Excuse me. Do you happen to have this book?

726
00:56:28.983 --> 00:56:30.354
("Although Nothing Will Change Even If You Cry")

727
00:56:30.653 --> 00:56:33.294
There was only one left in our stock and it was sold.

728
00:56:35.224 --> 00:56:36.423
Thank you.

729
00:56:44.474 --> 00:56:45.573
Yes.

730
00:56:46.434 --> 00:56:49.173
Hello, Father.

731
00:56:58.284 --> 00:57:01.423
You beat him up pretty hard.

732
00:57:02.854 --> 00:57:05.323
Will it be disadvantageous...

733
00:57:06.823 --> 00:57:07.994
to Ji Ho?

734
00:57:10.193 --> 00:57:11.564
I think it'll be fine.

735
00:57:12.463 --> 00:57:15.264
I met the CEO of his production company just now.

736
00:57:16.363 --> 00:57:19.704
We know each other. He won't make this bigger.

737
00:57:21.104 --> 00:57:23.403
Okay. Thank you.

738
00:57:28.213 --> 00:57:29.314
Well...

739
00:57:31.483 --> 00:57:33.314
The fact that I'm Ji Ho's husband...

740
00:57:34.553 --> 00:57:38.124
Will it affect you...

741
00:57:39.854 --> 00:57:41.423
in working with her?

742
00:57:42.593 --> 00:57:45.534
Is that why you're here?

743
00:57:47.903 --> 00:57:49.834
Are you worried I might ruin her work...

744
00:57:51.204 --> 00:57:53.503
because of the grudges from my old love?

745
00:57:54.544 --> 00:57:55.704
That I might harm her?

746
00:57:56.573 --> 00:57:57.573
Yes.

747
00:58:06.753 --> 00:58:08.184
When I got married,

748
00:58:08.954 --> 00:58:11.323
Ji Ho's mother asked me for this favor.

749
00:58:13.593 --> 00:58:16.124
She asked me to let her write...

750
00:58:17.064 --> 00:58:19.693
when she wants to begin her writing again...

751
00:58:21.704 --> 00:58:25.403
so that she doesn't give up on her dream.

752
00:58:26.434 --> 00:58:27.644
She asked me that.

753
00:58:30.644 --> 00:58:34.414
But I didn't know what to do,

754
00:58:36.584 --> 00:58:39.814
so I only promised her that I wouldn't be any harm to her.

755
00:58:42.084 --> 00:58:43.284
But...

756
00:58:45.923 --> 00:58:47.264
you know.

757
00:58:48.394 --> 00:58:49.564
You know...

758
00:58:50.934 --> 00:58:54.003
how to make her not give up on her dream.

759
00:58:58.303 --> 00:59:02.104
So you came to see me.

760
00:59:03.403 --> 00:59:06.414
You met your old love after 12 years,

761
00:59:07.584 --> 00:59:09.113
and is that what you have to say?

762
00:59:11.414 --> 00:59:13.213
I'm a bit upset.

763
00:59:15.523 --> 00:59:16.653
Sorry.

764
00:59:18.854 --> 00:59:20.093
But...

765
00:59:20.894 --> 00:59:23.264
there's really nothing I can do.

766
00:59:25.133 --> 00:59:27.363
I found out...

767
00:59:28.303 --> 00:59:29.863
why she gave up on writing today.

768
00:59:31.273 --> 00:59:33.943
The only thing I could do was throwing punches at him.

769
00:59:36.974 --> 00:59:38.773
I heard you're a good producer.

770
00:59:42.343 --> 00:59:43.414
Jung Min.

771
00:59:45.584 --> 00:59:47.053
Don't treat her as my wife,

772
00:59:48.124 --> 00:59:49.753
but as a writer,

773
00:59:51.193 --> 00:59:52.323
please.

774
00:59:58.564 --> 01:00:01.034
"Words are born from people's mouths..."

775
01:00:02.604 --> 01:00:04.573
"and die in their ears."

776
01:00:09.374 --> 01:00:11.943
("Although Nothing Will Change Even If You Cry")

777
01:00:14.213 --> 01:00:17.584
"But some words don't die."

778
01:00:18.184 --> 01:00:19.684
(Don't ever love again. You don't have the right to.)

779
01:00:19.684 --> 01:00:21.923
"They go into people's hearts..."

780
01:00:23.084 --> 01:00:24.494
"and survive."

781
01:00:26.593 --> 01:00:30.064
These words survived in my heart for 12 years.

782
01:00:30.994 --> 01:00:32.434
When did they disappear...

783
01:00:33.494 --> 01:00:35.463
so suddenly like this?

784
01:00:36.664 --> 01:00:38.303
I couldn't get rid of them...

785
01:00:39.633 --> 01:00:41.374
from my heart...

786
01:00:42.544 --> 01:00:44.113
no matter how hard I tried then.

787
01:00:49.284 --> 01:00:50.854
I have something to ask too.

788
01:00:54.053 --> 01:00:55.253
Have you...

789
01:00:56.023 --> 01:00:58.224
ever professed to Ms. Yoon before?

790
01:01:02.394 --> 01:01:03.523
What?

791
01:01:04.264 --> 01:01:05.434
Profession.

792
01:01:07.264 --> 01:01:09.363
That you like her.

793
01:01:11.073 --> 01:01:12.073
Or...

794
01:01:13.073 --> 01:01:16.204
something like that. Have you?

795
01:01:18.673 --> 01:01:22.514
I don't think it's necessary to express it with words.

796
01:01:22.684 --> 01:01:23.684
So you haven't.

797
01:01:24.914 --> 01:01:26.113
You know what?

798
01:01:27.153 --> 01:01:28.684
You never...

799
01:01:29.584 --> 01:01:31.454
did it to me either.

800
01:01:34.023 --> 01:01:35.093
You never said you liked me.

801
01:01:42.503 --> 01:01:44.503
-Bye. -Bye.

802
01:01:47.244 --> 01:01:48.474
Do you know...

803
01:01:50.544 --> 01:01:52.773
words can survive only when they reach people's hearts?

804
01:01:55.144 --> 01:01:58.014
You have to say it out loud for them to reach others' hearts.

805
01:01:59.713 --> 01:02:01.454
It wasn't a coincidence.

806
01:02:07.224 --> 01:02:08.463
So from now on,

807
01:02:10.093 --> 01:02:11.834
don't draw a line...

808
01:02:13.564 --> 01:02:14.834
on purpose.

809
01:02:15.564 --> 01:02:17.403
It was because of her words.

810
01:02:18.434 --> 01:02:21.144
I believe it's no one's fault.

811
01:02:23.773 --> 01:02:26.644
Just like some of those waves keep on flowing...

812
01:02:27.914 --> 01:02:31.213
while the others break.

813
01:02:34.954 --> 01:02:36.784
That's how it is.

814
01:02:37.653 --> 01:02:38.894
So...

815
01:02:40.093 --> 01:02:44.034
Her warm words piled up in my heart.

816
01:02:44.764 --> 01:02:46.164
Se Hee,

817
01:02:47.434 --> 01:02:49.403
don't worry too much.

818
01:02:52.573 --> 01:02:54.443
Just because you lived yesterday,

819
01:02:55.943 --> 01:02:57.644
it doesn't mean you know everything...

820
01:02:58.914 --> 01:03:00.273
about today.

821
01:03:03.044 --> 01:03:06.653
Her words have survived...

822
01:03:09.423 --> 01:03:10.693
(Us)

823
01:03:10.693 --> 01:03:11.994
in my dead heart.

824
01:03:11.994 --> 01:03:15.323
(Us)

825
01:03:18.294 --> 01:03:20.463
Do you still work part-time?

826
01:03:21.704 --> 01:03:22.863
Oh, yes.

827
01:03:23.633 --> 01:03:26.874
But I think I'll quit soon.

828
01:03:27.303 --> 01:03:29.544
That's nice to hear.

829
01:03:30.773 --> 01:03:31.843
Well...

830
01:03:32.974 --> 01:03:36.414
Once I quit this job, I plan to write again.

831
01:03:38.184 --> 01:03:40.514
What do you mean?

832
01:03:41.584 --> 01:03:42.653
That drama?

833
01:03:44.753 --> 01:03:45.823
Yes.

834
01:03:46.854 --> 01:03:48.423
I thought you quit writing...

835
01:03:48.994 --> 01:03:50.564
to focus on housekeeping.

836
01:03:51.733 --> 01:03:53.394
Yes, but...

837
01:03:54.233 --> 01:03:56.363
I got a nice opportunity,

838
01:03:56.834 --> 01:03:59.034
so I plan to begin writing again.

839
01:04:00.334 --> 01:04:01.443
What about a baby then?

840
01:04:02.374 --> 01:04:03.374
Pardon?

841
01:04:03.443 --> 01:04:05.213
When will you give birth?

842
01:04:09.443 --> 01:04:11.113
I'm not sure.

843
01:04:12.213 --> 01:04:15.153
I mean, work is important, but you should consider that too.

844
01:04:16.023 --> 01:04:18.923
You're still young, but Se Hee is not.

845
01:04:26.794 --> 01:04:28.503
Pay back his loan with this.

846
01:04:28.834 --> 01:04:31.403
Use the rest for housekeeping when you have a baby.

847
01:04:32.974 --> 01:04:35.374
- What? - I promised to give this money...

848
01:04:35.773 --> 01:04:36.943
when he got married.

849
01:04:41.744 --> 01:04:44.184
I don't think I should take this.

850
01:04:45.153 --> 01:04:46.354
Then who else?

851
01:04:48.584 --> 01:04:50.954
Of course, you should give this to Se Hee directly.

852
01:04:50.954 --> 01:04:53.354
We won't be able to talk.

853
01:04:53.823 --> 01:04:56.693
And he won't take it either. It's right for you to take it.

854
01:04:57.994 --> 01:05:00.604
It's important for you to be a bridge between family members...

855
01:05:01.164 --> 01:05:02.204
as his wife.

856
01:05:05.003 --> 01:05:06.204
Let's go.

857
01:05:06.534 --> 01:05:07.773
Father.

858
01:05:14.144 --> 01:05:16.014
I have something to say.

859
01:05:17.199 --> 01:05:18.728
It's cold, so go home safely.

860
01:05:40.688 --> 01:05:42.618
Where are you? Why aren't you coming?

861
01:05:42.688 --> 01:05:44.658
I'll go in shortly.

862
01:05:44.919 --> 01:05:47.129
Do you realize what time it is now? Come home already!

863
01:05:47.129 --> 01:05:48.759
Hey, I'm not a child.

864
01:05:49.058 --> 01:05:50.998
Don't overact, silly.

865
01:05:52.699 --> 01:05:53.768
See you later.

866
01:05:53.799 --> 01:05:56.069
- Stop being... - A mom?

867
01:05:57.899 --> 01:05:59.938
She seems happy though.

868
01:06:02.669 --> 01:06:03.779
Cheers!

869
01:06:10.009 --> 01:06:11.078
Soo Ji.

870
01:06:11.949 --> 01:06:13.679
Do you know the movie, "The Graduate"?

871
01:06:14.118 --> 01:06:17.049
Of course. Isn't that your favorite movie?

872
01:06:18.719 --> 01:06:20.958
I've seen it more than 10 times.

873
01:06:21.328 --> 01:06:24.129
When I first saw it, I was in my 10th grade.

874
01:06:24.528 --> 01:06:27.828
I fell for Ben when he went to Elaine's wedding...

875
01:06:28.969 --> 01:06:31.339
and ran away with her.

876
01:06:32.599 --> 01:06:33.738
It looked really romantic...

877
01:06:35.309 --> 01:06:39.208
to this 17-year-old girl.

878
01:06:39.939 --> 01:06:42.748
That's the most famous part of the movie, right?

879
01:06:43.948 --> 01:06:45.049
However,

880
01:06:46.278 --> 01:06:48.948
when I watched that movie again in my 20s,

881
01:06:49.889 --> 01:06:51.389
I could see many other things about the movie.

882
01:06:54.429 --> 01:06:55.559
Like what?

883
01:06:56.658 --> 01:06:58.299
Their faces after running out of the wedding venue.

884
01:07:01.828 --> 01:07:06.368
They ran away from the wedding with full of excitement.

885
01:07:08.309 --> 01:07:10.269
But somehow, they become speechless after getting on the bus.

886
01:07:12.439 --> 01:07:15.208
It looks like they are anxious and don't know what to do.

887
01:07:16.479 --> 01:07:18.379
I couldn't see that when I was young.

888
01:07:21.089 --> 01:07:23.448
But I can see that now.

889
01:07:28.528 --> 01:07:29.689
Why?

890
01:07:30.599 --> 01:07:31.998
Is it something you can see...

891
01:07:32.099 --> 01:07:34.429
between you and your landlord?

892
01:07:43.879 --> 01:07:45.009
Is it hard for you?

893
01:07:51.419 --> 01:07:52.519
Yes, it is.

894
01:08:09.769 --> 01:08:10.868
Hello.

895
01:08:12.339 --> 01:08:13.439
Now?

896
01:08:14.868 --> 01:08:16.009
Okay.

897
01:08:19.139 --> 01:08:20.849
It's really cold now.

898
01:08:21.708 --> 01:08:22.908
You should go now.

899
01:08:24.578 --> 01:08:25.948
Don't worry about me.

900
01:08:27.318 --> 01:08:29.419
You can go now. Mr. Ma is waiting for you.

901
01:08:30.519 --> 01:08:33.189
Text me when you get home.

902
01:08:48.839 --> 01:08:51.479
What's going on? Are you okay?

903
01:08:51.639 --> 01:08:53.408
What's wrong?

904
01:08:53.979 --> 01:08:56.309
Did you do something to Mr. Park?

905
01:08:56.479 --> 01:08:58.479
Well, your way didn't work out well.

906
01:08:58.479 --> 01:09:00.179
So I figured my own way out.

907
01:09:00.719 --> 01:09:02.648
What did you do?

908
01:09:02.889 --> 01:09:04.488
I punched him in the face.

909
01:09:06.719 --> 01:09:07.828
What?

910
01:09:08.389 --> 01:09:10.828
Well done. Come here!

911
01:09:13.868 --> 01:09:14.969
Come here!

912
01:09:22.568 --> 01:09:24.879
I realized it when I found love.

913
01:09:26.009 --> 01:09:28.248
The reason our marriage happened easily was...

914
01:09:30.078 --> 01:09:32.919
because we were not in love.

915
01:09:33.748 --> 01:09:36.889
I will pay for the half of your dress expense.

916
01:09:36.889 --> 01:09:39.919
It's okay. It didn't cost me that much anyway.

917
01:09:39.919 --> 01:09:43.158
But you even had to pay for the shoes and the bouquet.

918
01:09:43.158 --> 01:09:45.799
I will deduct those expenses from your next month's rent.

919
01:09:46.599 --> 01:09:49.169
Marriage should happen when you are in love.

920
01:09:50.068 --> 01:09:51.169
But why...

921
01:09:51.498 --> 01:09:53.939
(Inseong Bank)

922
01:09:54.538 --> 01:09:57.038
When are you going to give birth?

923
01:09:59.009 --> 01:10:01.078
Am I getting hurt more...

924
01:10:01.879 --> 01:10:04.519
when I'm in love with him?

925
01:10:14.129 --> 01:10:16.158
Have you told Ji Ho you like her?

926
01:10:16.488 --> 01:10:20.129
Do you know that you actually have to say it to let her know?

927
01:10:20.799 --> 01:10:23.868
You have to speak it out. That's the only way it will reach her heart.

928
01:10:25.398 --> 01:10:28.439
I know. It's really awkward.

929
01:10:30.738 --> 01:10:32.208
But it looks better...

930
01:10:33.979 --> 01:10:35.208
than I expected.

931
01:10:38.919 --> 01:10:40.049
Let's do it well...

932
01:10:41.519 --> 01:10:42.748
today.

933
01:11:03.009 --> 01:11:04.809
Have you been to Soo Ji's place?

934
01:11:05.738 --> 01:11:09.509
Yes. I had beer with her.

935
01:11:10.748 --> 01:11:12.049
I see.

936
01:11:27.998 --> 01:11:31.398
Did you sign the contract today?

937
01:11:32.498 --> 01:11:33.599
I did.

938
01:11:34.169 --> 01:11:37.408
She's such a nice person.

939
01:11:38.078 --> 01:11:39.179
I see.

940
01:11:40.608 --> 01:11:41.708
That's good to know.

941
01:11:46.379 --> 01:11:48.589
You look very tired.

942
01:11:49.788 --> 01:11:52.919
I'm exhausted.

943
01:11:53.828 --> 01:11:54.988
It's pretty bad today.

944
01:12:07.169 --> 01:12:10.408
Kitty, you are welcoming us today.

945
01:12:14.979 --> 01:12:18.049
I have something to tell you.

946
01:12:18.379 --> 01:12:22.948
I have something to tell you too.

947
01:12:34.129 --> 01:12:35.868
Can she not see this well?

948
01:13:01.059 --> 01:13:02.488
- I want to... - We...

949
01:13:06.398 --> 01:13:07.898
You can tell me first.

950
01:13:08.669 --> 01:13:11.639
Okay. So...

951
01:13:12.799 --> 01:13:14.139
Can we...

952
01:13:21.809 --> 01:13:24.618
Never mind. You can tell me first.

953
01:13:28.919 --> 01:13:30.248
I would like to...

954
01:13:34.089 --> 01:13:35.358
end our...

955
01:13:40.028 --> 01:13:42.328
contract now.

956
01:13:45.969 --> 01:13:49.009
Words are always...

957
01:13:51.979 --> 01:13:53.238
slower than...

958
01:13:58.748 --> 01:13:59.948
the heart.

959
01:14:20.238 --> 01:14:23.879
(Because This Is My First Life)

960
01:14:24.908 --> 01:14:28.509
The more the love deepened, the more confused I got.

961
01:14:29.509 --> 01:14:30.778
Isn't that Ho Rang?

962
01:14:30.778 --> 01:14:32.748
She looked like a shivering chick in the morning.

963
01:14:32.748 --> 01:14:35.889
Which sentence is the least corny if I want to tell her my feelings?

964
01:14:36.089 --> 01:14:38.719
Who could be Mr. Ma's friend's friend's friend?

965
01:14:39.059 --> 01:14:42.028
It's me. Do you want to go on a date with me?

966
01:14:44.059 --> 01:14:46.398
What do you think marriage is?

967
01:14:47.429 --> 01:14:49.099
Do you have any idea, Se Hee?

968
01:14:49.498 --> 01:14:53.169
Getting married when you are in love must be happy, right?

969
01:14:53.368 --> 01:14:56.809
(Us)

